    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="1226"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1226">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/317.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul General <persName type="from">Hanna</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate General</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Monterey</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 5, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Very favorable answers have been received from the Secretary of Hacienda relative
                    to my representations made to General Carranza in behalf of the Huasteca Oil
                    Company, the matter of exchange, kind of money to be accepted, clearance of oil
                    ships and American oil interests. I have telegraphed Consul Miller at
                    Tampico.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
